rComments: Most amazing prof I have ever had! If you can take him!

His class was great! He's a very interesting professor! He is very helpful and definitely wants everyone to succeed! Hes willing to give extensions if you ask for it. The final take-home examination was rather long (like writing 4 mini essays) but then again it was easy and straightforward so that was okay. I would love to have him as a prof again!

Most amazing prof I ever had in university. I wish I could have had all my classes with him. He is very helpful, treats you like an equal, and is very knowledgable. Fair grader, not too harsh, and wants his students to do well.

This class is a disaster with a professor who has no teaching experience and talks to the class as if we are on his level. Regret taking this class with Page and now have a deep hatred for this program. Projects are very difficult to understand. Avoid if you can.

I just took his class for the first time. He was inspiring, quotable, engaging, interesting and has experience like no other, being that he was the first ever Parliamentary Budget Officer (PBO) in Canadian history. I recommend taking him extremely highly!
